div1.p:
Similar assertions of the unity of God are found in

Deut. iv. 35, 39 ('Jehovah is the God; there is none else beside him');

2 Sam. vii. 22;

xxii. 32;

1 Kings viii. 60;

I Chron. xvii. 20;

Psa. xviii. 31 ('Who is God save Jehovah? or who is a rock save our God?');

Psa. lxxxvi. 10 ('Thou art God alone');

Isa. xliii. 10-12;

xliv. 6, 8;

xlv. 22;

Joel ii. 27;

Zech. xiv. 9.

The New Testament confirms this doctrine repeatedly:

Mark xii. 29;

John xvii. 3 ('Thee, the only true God');

1 Cor. viii. 4 ('There is none other God but one');

Gal. iii. 20;

1 Tim. ii. 5.

