The first article of the Creed speaks of God as the prime 
origin, more particularly of the first Person of the Holy Trinity, God the
Father, and of God as the Creator of the world;

It is taken from the following words of the Prophet Isaiah : Behold, a virgin shall conceive, and bear a Son, and they shall call his name Immanuel, which, being interpreted, is, God with us.
Isaiah vii. 14;
Matt. i. 23.

In the time of the Old Testament, infants were circumcised when 
eight days old; but Baptism in the New Testament takes the place of circumcision; 
consequently infants should also be baptized.

